review_blob: The bottle and the deScription depict a light beer, the color says, perhaps a hint of wheat, and the label states spice, when I sip it, its all hops? Terrible labeling decent beer, but nothing special, dominated by hops.
Decent, not unenjoyable in anyway, but far from good or great. Too thin for a pumpkin, needs more mouth feel. Good balance of flavor levels, but the taste is a touch synthetic.
Nice, not much of an aroma, very, very thick wheat without an overly wheaty flavor. Mild banana, cloves, touch of coffee flavor. Excellent wheat beer, you should drink this.
Thick, super whearty beer, pretty darn good. Love the mouth feel. Typically Banana and cloves flavor, not as sweet as some of its competitors which I appreciate.

Nice aroma, and great appearance, think with perfect looking bubbles. Taste sweet banana, touch of spice. Good beer, but not great, wish it got rid of the touch of sweetness. Still happy with this purchase.
mmm... Very nice, perfect mouth feel, not much of a smell. Taste wise, lots of lemony which is a big surprise.

Solid beer, good flavor, easy to drink. Wish it was a bit thicker/had more mouth feel. Flavor, lemon and orange mix with a noticeable alcohol flavor. After half a bottle Im also catching a twinge of pepper as well. This is a good beer, which is frustrating to me, as with some slight tweaks it could be great.
This beer is very good. Balanced, wheat, banana, flavor, minor citrus as well. This beer is perfectly balanced, easy to drink yet fulfilling at the same time.
Strong synthetic Blue Berry taste overpowers this beer, completely one note. Too sweet to work.

Apple nutmeg beer, go figure. Surprised I liked it as much as I did. The smell and taste are strong and similarly, of apples, cinnamon, nutmeg, hint of brown sugar. Good fall/winter beer. Happy to have 1 or 2 of these in a session any more would be flavor overload.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Very minor aroma, Tastes super citrus, powerful citrus! solid beer wish it had a bit more body.
Ok, mouth feel, strong Banana smell, flavor is good, strong banana and vanilla. Not great, but definitely good.
light bodied for the style, mediciny flavor, not worth too much thought. Buy something else.
small hops flavor moves into slight creamy lemon flavor. Decent beer, which it was a bit more creamy, and a bit less hoppy.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: What the hell is this lol? A strong, thick wheat beer with powerful coffee and chocolate flavoring, without being sweat in any way. Actually this is really good, I will buy again!

Very little aroma, slight hops, ginger. Taste, smooth- wheat and ginger as advertised. This blend goes together very well, the aroma and appearance of this beer dont do justice to the well balanced and rewarding flavor that ensues.
Smells of green apple, highly carbonated, champagne like bubbles never seem to end. Taste, hint of apple, caramel, banana, Delicious. This is a really good beer.
Solid summer beer, good for a hot day. light mouthfeel, lemon sent goes to obviously lemon flavor. Not sweet which is good, wish it was thicker.

Decent oatmeal stout, obviously flavors of oatmeal, chocolate bit nutty. Milder flavor for this variety, somewhat smooth. Good, but wish it was bolder, made to appeal to the masses and it will do that.
Decent beer, Smooth banana, vanilla, orange flavor. Mild flavor, a touch watery. Very little aftertaste. Light mouthfeel for the varietal.
Tastes like a watered down pale ale, smells nice but all down hill from there.

wow, great surprise in this offering, Wheat, clove, mild banana, vanilla and a hint of butterscotch come through. A very nice brew, I could drink allot of this! Also, the more I drink this the more I like it!!!!
Powerful flavor, thick beer, flavor lots of banana, some caramel without being sweet, hint of vanilla on the back. Great after taste, leaves you wanting more. This is a very good beer :)
Consistent easy to find wit beer. Hint of lemon and orange, pure citrus after taste. Well balanced, not too heavy, not too light. I drink this quite often :)
Wow, this is excellent. highly carbonated, apple flavoring is minor, spot on. Not too sweet, absolutely delicious!!!! This may be the best fruit flavored beer Ive ever had.
Indiscriminate spice and fruit flavor, citrus dominant with a hint of hops, doesnt quite come together. Not bad, but not too good either.

This beer lacks flavor and character big time. Its the Coors light of wheat beers. Theres nothing good or bad about this beers flavor. Perhaps this would be a good beer to get someone into something with more of a mouth feel than a big brand light beer, or a good beer to chug, other than that Ive got no use for this.
Hints of clove and banana, with a scent of lemon on the nose.... strong flavor, this beer does not hold back. Not my favorite Unibroue beer, but still very good.
Nothing special, but not bad.. somewhat sweet, soy sauce flavor abounds, decent mouth-feel
